(218, 1, '2014-08-14 18:17:07', '2014-08-14 10:17:07', '<h2><span style="color: #0000ff;">Pattern for safety of imported dairy products takes shape</span></h2>\r\n<h3><strong><span style="color: #000000;">进口乳制品安全格局初定</span></strong></h3>\r\n<h3><span style="color: #3366ff;">International Business Daily by n/a 24 June 2014</span></h3>\r\nOverseas manufacturers without registration in China are no longer able to export their dairy products to the Chinese mainland market, as new regulations came into effect as of May 1. According to the General Administration of Quality Supervision, Inspection and Quarantine (AQSIQ), China had already certified 1,122 foreign dairy producers, including 41 companies which make infant milk formula. Industry insiders said the new regulations will ensure safety of imported milk powder and cause certain influence on China''s industrial pattern. In addition, China also forbade distributing infant milk powder imported in large packages. The imported powder must already be packed into small packages before sold to consumers. The package requirement can ensure the safety of imported milk powder sold in China.\r\n从5月1日起，我国全面实施对进口乳品境外生产企业的注册管理。未经注册的境外企业生产的乳品不得进口。根据国家质检总局公布的信息，首批通过注册的进口乳品生产企业共有1122家乳品境外生产企业，其中婴幼儿配方奶粉生产企业41家。业内人士表示，这一进口乳品新规有利于保障进口奶粉的安全，同时也会对海外奶粉在我国的产业格局造成一定的影响。此外，从5月1日起，我国严禁进口大包装婴幼儿配方乳粉到境内分装，必须已罐装在向消费者出售的最小零售包装中。这样是为了从源头上保证国内销售的进口乳粉符合中国食品安全。', '文章2', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '202-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-08-14 18:17:07', '2014-08-14 10:17:07', '', 202, 'http://wordpress.local/archives/218', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
