(265, 1, '2014-08-20 18:40:06', '2014-08-20 10:40:06', 'The total value of China''s food imports in the first quarter of this year increased by 95.35% year-on-year. China National Light IndustryInformationCenter revealed on June 24 that imports of dairy products, which accounted for 78.4% of total food imports, increased by 126.76% year-on-year. Sugar imports, which accounted for 11.3% of total food imports, increased by 40.3% year-on-year. The main food import sources in the first quarter include New Zealand, Brazil, the US, Australia, France, Germany, South Korea,Argentina, Cuba and Malaysia. The value of food imported from New Zealand, which accounted for 59.5% of the total value of food imports, increased by 130.75% year-on-year.\r\n中国食品行业今年一季度累计进口额同比增长95.35%。中国轻工业信息中心24日透露，从各子行业进口情况来看，乳品累计进口额占食品进口总额的78.4%，同比增长126.76%；糖累计进口占11.3%，同比约增长40.3%。一季度食品主要进口来源国家有新西兰、巴西、美国、澳大利亚、法国、德国、韩国、阿根廷、古巴、马来西亚等。其中，由新西兰进口额占食品进口总额的59.5%，同比增长130.75%。', 'event1', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'event1', '', '', '2014-09-01 12:51:17', '2014-09-01 04:51:17', '', 0, 'http://wordpress.local/?p=265', 0, 'post', '', 0),
